# macOS
.DS_Store
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# Editors
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Stray editor/tool backups — never committed
*.bak
*.bak-*

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Claude — this repo carries no committed project-scoped settings (the whole
# `.claude/` dir is local-only). User/global config lives in `dot-claude/`,
# symlinked into ~/.claude/ by `dot sync`. Machine-local overrides stay
# untracked via `**/.claude/settings.local.json` below.
.claude/

# Secrets resolve through `op run --` / op:// references, never a file (see
# CLAUDE.md). `.npmrc` is gitignored at the user-config level because per-project
# `.npmrc`s belong to those projects' repos (with op:// refs if they need
# credentials). A user-level `.npmrc` would mostly hold registry-auth
# state we don't want bleeding across projects.
.npmrc

# Transient/generated
Brewfile.lock.json

# Generated audit reports (gnar audit plugin) — regenerate on demand, not tracked.
audit/

# Machine-specific overrides
dot-claude/settings.local.json
**/.claude/settings.local.json
